HEADWORD: Permanency
<hw>Per"ma*nen*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>permanence</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
permanent; continuance in the same state or place; duration; fixedness;
<as>as, the <ex>permanence</ex> of institutions; the <ex>permanence</ex>
of nature.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Permanent</ent>⟦br⟧
